 Starting from APK v1.22.x, users can enable automatic blurring of PII (Personally Identifiable Information). PII includes blurring of vehicle registration plates and pedestrians, in all media (video and image) streams that contain Road side stream like event videos, DVR requests, periodic-Image-Captures.     One can specify to blur vehicle registration plates appearing in all road streams by default through the blurPII key in asset configuration (this can be changed at asset level, apart from Fleet and Account level):  (Deprecated from v1.23)      {
  // ... other configuration fields
  blurPII: true // Boolean : true / false
}  From v1.23, the equivalent configuration key to set the above behavior will be:     "blurConfig": {
       "roadBlurPII": true
}      Additionally, one can specify to blur registration plates while creating DVR requests, this will override the above asset configuration (this is applicable for DVR, EDVR and CDVR requests).      { .. "blurPII" : true // Boolean : true / false .. }  NOTE the following:    blurPII DVR request body key is supported only for trips taken from APK v1.22.x and higher, hence if the request is for a trip taken with APK version prior to v1.22.x, with blurPII key present and is true or false, the DVR request will get fulfilled without any PII blurring if data is avaialble.       If DVR is requested with blurPII key false, then irrespective of the asset configuration flag (blurPII), the DVR video will be fulfilled without any PII blurring. With this one can get unblurred footage for any video, provided the video is available on the device.        If DVR Request is for a trip taken with APK version prior to v1.22.x, without blurPII key present in the DVR request body, request will be fulfilled without any blur.       If DVR Request is for a trip taken with APK version v1.22.x or above, and without blurPII key present in the DVR request body, then the PII blurring falls back on the asset configuration key: blurPII when the trip was started.        This solution relies on reliable vehicle and pedestrian detections from AI module. Hence, might have occasional misses.       This solution is NOT supported on Jimi devices. It is supported on all Mitac devices (K245, K220 and K265) and also on STSunlab device ST9730. This will be supported in a future release.     PII blurring is not supported during live streaming.       PII blurring is more focussed on objects that are closer to our vehicle rather than those that are far away. Hence, objects that are far away may not be blurred since PII itself may not be visible         KNOWN ISSUES:      Since the blurring depends on detection of vehicles and pedestrians through AI models, the performance (Blurring Accuracy i.e. number of relevant objects getting blurred) may be sub-optimal under the following conditions   Low light conditions (ex: basement).  On vehicles in the opposite flow of traffic with a divider in between.  Occasionally when the vehicles or pedestrians are too close or the vehicle orientations are different (ex: in a parking lot) or lower-half of the pedestrian is occluded.  The accuracy could also be lower in single-image capture as compared to videos, since temporal information that is used in blurring videos is not available.  Since the focus is to blur as many closer objects as possible, there could be some false blurring too (i.e. blurring in regions where there are no pedestrians or vehicles).
